These containers provide a link from Superset -> mongobi -> mongodb

The compose file starts the following containers
- superset		172.30.0.10
- mongobi		172.30.0.11
- superset-redis	172.30.0.12
- superset-db		172.30.0.13
- superset-init 	172.30.0.14	(just initializes the first time and exits)

Connection fields for the monbobi are set in the .env file

Once running, add the database connection within superset with the following connection string to your mongobi container:
mongobi://mongobi:3307/<your_db>

# to run the first time
docker compose up -d
docker compose --profile init run --rm superset-init

# to run subsequent times, just run
docker compose up -d


# use the following after changes to be sure they are implemented
docker compose down
docker compose build --no-cache superset superset-init
docker compose up -d
docker compose --profile init run --rm superset-init


